claim.claim-text:
A computer-implemented method for disabling a vehicle horn, the computer-implemented method comprising:
receiving at a vehicle computer a location of a vehicle;
receiving at the vehicle computer a location of one or more points along a route where a vehicle horn is disabled;
based on the location of the vehicle and the location of the one or more vehicle horn disabling points, determining at the vehicle computer that the vehicle is in the vicinity of the one or more vehicle horn disabling points; and
transmitting one or more instructions from the vehicle computer to disable the vehicle horn when in the vicinity of the one or more vehicle horn disabling points.

The system of claim 7 wherein the at least one vehicle computer configured to receive information identifying the location of the vehicle is configured to:
receive one or more images of one or more road signs identifying the one or more horn disabling locations;
process the one or more images for identifying that the vehicle is in the vicinity of the one or more horn disabling locations.
